over twice our level, deep red, we had no gear because the server just popped...  We defied the odds and did what people usually don't do.  My group consisted of the highest levels on server by the time we were through - the funny thing about this is we didn't give a shit about being the highest levels on server... we were just having fun.<br><br>I am *NOT* talking about being &quot;UBER&quot; or being the fastest leveler... I'm talking about risk vs reward.  The bigger the risk, the more the reward.  Honestly, no, it's not even about the reward, it is about the rush, the feeling of doing what everyone else believes to be suicide.     <br><br>People are just sooo use to believeing that things can only get done in one way when they grow in levels.  So maybe some dumb ass group went into PoF without an enchanter and got wiped out?  Who's to say that would happen again?  Different people, different strategies, different times.  <br><br>I went with a group into PoG the other day with no cleric.  One necro, one shaman, one wizard, 2 sks, and 1 warrior.  Now it's not like we're all &quot;uber&quot;... most of the group was under lvl 55...  and we were killing mobs non stop... fast and fun.  (it wasn't even hard... but if I had asked some random person to come join me that didn't know me, they'd think I was nuts... PoG with no cleric?  wth is wrong with you?)<br><br>I mean I understand there are people that are safe, that are cautious, that don't like risks... but I'm just saying, where the hell did the rest of you go???  I also understand that there is also a time and a place for the safe and cautious but to me, it just seems that there's no longer a time for any risk and danger?  What's going on?<br><br>______________________<br>There's a difference between the impossible and the improbable....<br><br>(Oh yeah, I can't forget to do this.  KUDOS and a shout out to everyone that joined me in PoG (Yugisha, Ephelba, Kanr, Notuanot, Dvara)!  I love you all!  It's awesome that ya came along and I hope you all had fun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    ) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usneez.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sneez</A> at: 8/20/02 2:00:41 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utzarothfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tzaroth FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 213<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/20/02 1:05:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1245.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The safe, the cautious, the normal... the ARGHHH!!!</span><hr size=1> Several times have I fought in a group scenario against monsters that were almost twice our level. And typically, only one of us survived or none at all, but it was worth it to me. I've said it before and I'll say it again, I have no experience with the raiding game: however, I'd imagine that the thrill of doing the nigh-impossible doesn't wear off with age. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usneez.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sneez</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/20/02 1:06:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1245.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The safe, the cautious, the normal... the ARGHHH!!!</span><hr size=1> Aye, but as ya get into the 50-60's it just seems rare to find people willing to take a risk...  Oh who cares if you die a couple times?  Have fun 