tunately with our healing power severly crippled these are no longer options. I played main healer for 2 groups in Kaesora this weekend and I can tell you I was bored as hell.  If we had just one enchanter I would have suggested trying to AOEing and as a shaman I hate AOE.<br><br>So while I agree with Sneez in general there are certain levels and encounters where because of the design of the game the holy trinity is neseccary.  I do think some of my funnest times in EQ have involved groups that were unconventional.  ie. 49 bard and 2 46 druids vs. Gullerback,  5 39+ rangers and a 39 druid in Mistmoore.  One of my most memorable experiences was a 45 shaman, 46 druid, and 51(?) ranger doing TT cycle.  The rangers job was to ensnare and root.  Once we had doted the mob to 1/2 the ranger would just hate kite until he got aggro and then root and back away.  That night in TT we got:  Sigma's belt(sp), Ghastly Robe, Iksar BP, Hangman's Noose, 3 OS keys, and the hardest pull of the night the stupid Yun Shaman with the black powder for Canni II.<br><br>Targor<br>44 shaman <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usneez.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sneez</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/20/02 3:20:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1245.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: The safe, the cautious, the normal... the ARGHHH!!!</span><hr size=1> I applaud you for your challenges you have faced... but whenever I go on some challenge I never make it unefficient.  I don't turn myself into a cleric by just chain healing mobs.  Use what ya have to your advantage.  <br><br>Although it was an ak